WEBVTT

00:05.506 --> 00:07.041
WADE: That's why you stopped
 our little frolic

00:07.075 --> 00:08.376
the other night?
 You got googly eyes

00:08.409 --> 00:09.510
for golden boy George?

00:09.543 --> 00:10.678
Do you really
think that about me?

00:10.711 --> 00:12.513
That I'm snobbish
and shallow?

00:12.546 --> 00:13.381
Zoe knows about us.

00:13.414 --> 00:14.615
George, Lavon and I

00:14.648 --> 00:16.650
had an affair;
I cannot tell you

00:16.684 --> 00:18.486
how sorry I am.
You don't have to.

00:18.519 --> 00:19.553
'Cause it's over.

00:19.587 --> 00:21.455
Yes, I swear to you it...
Lemon.

00:21.489 --> 00:22.523
I meant us.

00:22.556 --> 00:23.791
No.
 I didn't want to be

00:23.824 --> 00:25.126
in the middle of all of this.

00:25.159 --> 00:26.394
I understand, yeah.

00:26.427 --> 00:27.428
Except one thing,

00:27.461 --> 00:28.862
we're not friends.

00:32.665 --> 00:34.868
(shower starts)

00:48.416 --> 00:50.784
Who the...

00:58.659 --> 01:01.129
Uh-oh.

01:01.929 --> 01:03.964
(sighs)
George knows.

01:03.997 --> 01:06.667
Months of keeping
the big secret,

01:06.700 --> 01:08.869
and now, ka-bam,
it's exploded.

01:08.902 --> 01:10.838
Who knows what the
fallout's gonna be?

01:10.871 --> 01:12.606
All the belles
could be wearing black.

01:12.640 --> 01:14.275
Yeah, well, all I know
is I blew it.

01:14.308 --> 01:16.710
Kissing Lemon in public.

01:16.744 --> 01:18.412
Monumentally stupid.

01:18.446 --> 01:19.580
And George Tucker...

01:19.613 --> 01:22.015
Poor George.
Yeah.

01:22.049 --> 01:23.317
(grunts)

01:25.453 --> 01:26.554
What are you doing?

01:26.587 --> 01:27.588
George is hurt and angry.

01:27.621 --> 01:28.956
He already lashed out at me.

01:28.989 --> 01:30.458
It's obvious that you
will be the next target.

01:30.491 --> 01:33.427
I just want you to be prepared.

01:33.461 --> 01:34.562
(grunts)

01:34.595 --> 01:36.330
Okay, you know I got hit

01:36.364 --> 01:38.999
by 350-pound linemen
for a living, right?

01:39.032 --> 01:39.833
Mm-hmm.

01:39.867 --> 01:40.968
Those little jabs are just

01:41.001 --> 01:43.404
like butterflies dancing
on my chest.

01:43.437 --> 01:44.872
And no offense to George,

01:44.905 --> 01:46.940
not exactly afraid
of his right hook, either.

01:46.974 --> 01:48.008
Though he's got

01:48.041 --> 01:49.343
a right to try.
I'm gonna go

01:49.377 --> 01:51.078
to the Rammer Jammer
and do some recon.

01:51.111 --> 01:53.481
Find out what everyone's
saying about the big breakup.

01:53.514 --> 01:56.417
You should probably lay
low until I report back.

01:58.051 --> 02:00.754
Hey, uh,
I need y'all's help.

02:00.788 --> 02:01.822
Why would I help you?

02:01.855 --> 02:03.191
Why would I help anyone?

02:03.224 --> 02:04.858
I am a shallow
snob, remember?

02:04.892 --> 02:06.294
Move out of my way.

02:06.327 --> 02:08.429
Ow.

02:08.461 --> 02:10.431
Lavon...

02:10.464 --> 02:11.565
Wait, write it down.

02:11.599 --> 02:13.066
If you do your
laundry once a week,

02:13.100 --> 02:14.635
you won't have
to borrow my socks.

02:14.668 --> 02:16.270
Yeah, or your underwear.

02:16.304 --> 02:17.037
My what now?

02:17.070 --> 02:18.339
Look, it doesn't matter.

02:18.372 --> 02:19.873
Point is there's
an emergency, all right?

02:19.907 --> 02:22.009
Last night, regrettably,
I got very drunk,

02:22.042 --> 02:24.044
and, uh, I slept
with someone.

02:24.077 --> 02:26.480
So, that happens
all the time.

02:26.514 --> 02:27.748
Well, I can't remember who.

02:27.781 --> 02:29.016
And that happens
most of the time.

02:29.049 --> 02:31.452
Yeah, but none
of my other overnight guests

02:31.485 --> 02:32.653
wear things...

02:32.686 --> 02:35.489
(clears throat)
...like this.

02:35.523 --> 02:37.891
That is a large garment.

02:37.925 --> 02:40.060
She's in my shower right now.

02:40.093 --> 02:42.530
Are you sure she could
fit in your shower?

02:42.563 --> 02:44.298
What are we gonna do?

02:44.332 --> 02:47.801
You are gonna head back home
and meet your new girlfriend.

02:47.835 --> 02:48.936
Bring her a doughnut.

02:48.969 --> 02:51.605
Come with me. Please.

02:51.639 --> 02:53.607
Go.

02:53.641 --> 02:54.942
You're a good friend.

02:54.975 --> 02:56.944
Thank you, thank you so much.

02:56.977 --> 02:58.111
You made your bed.

02:58.145 --> 02:59.713
Hope she didn't break it.

02:59.747 --> 03:01.849
MEN (a capella):
* Come, friends

03:01.882 --> 03:03.617
* Who plough the sea

03:03.651 --> 03:05.686
* Truce to navigation

03:05.719 --> 03:07.555
* Take another station

03:07.588 --> 03:10.824
* Let's vary piracy

03:10.858 --> 03:13.794
* With a little burglary

03:13.827 --> 03:16.063
Hey, Shelsters,

03:16.096 --> 03:17.565
wh-what's going on, huh?

03:17.598 --> 03:18.666
Any news? Any gossip?

03:18.699 --> 03:20.568
Debbie Jean Fordham
got laryngitis

03:20.601 --> 03:23.704
and can't perform
on Dash DeWitt's charity revue,

03:23.737 --> 03:25.773
"Gilbert and South-ivan"
tomorrow.

03:25.806 --> 03:27.808
Gilbert and South-ivan?

03:27.841 --> 03:30.378
And that's the gossip?
The only gossip?

03:30.411 --> 03:32.346
Sorry, geez.

03:35.716 --> 03:36.917
Hey, Brick.

03:38.752 --> 03:39.720
How you holding up?

03:39.753 --> 03:41.489
What do you think?

03:41.522 --> 03:43.357
I am so furious,
I can't even see straight.

03:43.391 --> 03:45.225
I'm sorry, I heard.
(sighs)

03:45.259 --> 03:47.227
Yeah, but after a while,
this anger will pass.
No, it won't,

03:47.261 --> 03:49.463
not before I have to get up
and sing tomorrow night.

03:49.497 --> 03:50.631
Sing?
Do you know

03:50.664 --> 03:51.999
how many words there are

03:52.032 --> 03:54.201
in "I Am a Very Model
of a Modern Major General"?

03:54.234 --> 03:56.270
There's ten
in the title alone.

03:56.304 --> 03:59.273
I can't believe I let Dash
convince me to sign up for this.

03:59.307 --> 04:01.409
Right.

04:01.442 --> 04:04.412
Dash, now he is
always causing trouble.

04:11.719 --> 04:13.153
I still don't understand.

04:13.186 --> 04:15.723
How is this cake gonna make
George un-break up with you?

04:15.756 --> 04:17.156
Oh, he didn't
break up with me.

04:17.190 --> 04:19.192
He was angry,
and he lashed out,

04:19.226 --> 04:20.728
but he didn't mean it.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.496
And how do you know?

04:22.530 --> 04:23.931
You see this?

04:23.964 --> 04:24.832
Mm-hmm.

04:24.865 --> 04:26.500
Zero calls, you know why?

04:26.534 --> 04:27.701
Because George

04:27.735 --> 04:28.836
has not told anyone.

04:28.869 --> 04:30.103
Not even a single soul.

04:30.137 --> 04:31.905
Had he even insinuated
that we were fighting,

04:31.939 --> 04:34.308
that phone would be
ringing off the hook

04:34.342 --> 04:36.043
with people wanting
in on the gossip.

04:36.076 --> 04:37.745
Maybe he hasn't had
a chance to tell anyone.

04:37.778 --> 04:38.746
It just happened.

04:38.779 --> 04:40.147
Maybe.

04:40.180 --> 04:42.750
But until then, I have hopes
that he will reconsider.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.652
So this morning,
I am bringing him

04:44.685 --> 04:47.154
his favorite cake,
and I'm going to apologize.

04:47.187 --> 04:48.589
What's he so angry about anyway?

04:48.622 --> 04:51.058
I never heard what you
guys were fighting about.

04:51.091 --> 04:52.460
It's not important.

04:52.493 --> 04:54.428
Because all today
and all tomorrow,

04:54.462 --> 04:56.997
during Dash's revue,
I'm going to apologize.

04:57.030 --> 04:58.532
And I will not stop,

04:58.566 --> 05:01.369
and eventually,
he will have to forgive me.

05:07.875 --> 05:09.910
Uh...

05:09.943 --> 05:11.178
Hello?

05:11.211 --> 05:12.546
TOM:
Hey, Wade.
(screams)

05:13.681 --> 05:14.782
(both screaming)

05:14.815 --> 05:16.717
Why are we screaming?

05:16.750 --> 05:18.686
What are you doing here?
Don't you remember?

05:18.719 --> 05:20.688
I wouldn't be asking, Tom,
if I remembered.

05:20.721 --> 05:22.923
I found you last night walking
on the side of the road.

05:22.956 --> 05:24.291
You were drunk as a skunk.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.360
So I brought you back here,
and I was tired,

05:26.394 --> 05:27.495
so I slept over.

05:27.528 --> 05:28.762
In my bed?

05:28.796 --> 05:29.963
The couch was itchy.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.832
Don't worry, we
slept feet to head.

05:31.865 --> 05:34.435
Eh, some things are best forgot.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.303
Tom, uh...

05:36.336 --> 05:39.640
can you tell me
whose shirt this is?

05:39.673 --> 05:41.709
Maybe what I was doing
by the side of the road?

05:41.742 --> 05:43.010
I have no idea.

05:43.043 --> 05:44.311
This is intriguing.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.381
And where's my car, Tom?
You lost your car?

05:47.415 --> 05:50.317
Oh, man, this is just
like The Hangover,

05:50.350 --> 05:52.920
which is awesome, because it's
exactly like The Hangover 2.

05:52.953 --> 05:55.489
There might be a tiger
in your closet.

05:58.025 --> 06:00.060
I'm going over there.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.128
He needs a friend.

06:01.161 --> 06:02.195
A friend?

06:02.229 --> 06:03.397
He's not even speaking to you.

06:03.431 --> 06:05.599
George just thinks
he's mad at me.

06:05.633 --> 06:06.800
He needs someone today.

06:06.834 --> 06:09.470
Someone who understands
what he's going through.

06:09.503 --> 06:10.971
You're not trying to use
this to your advantage?

06:11.004 --> 06:12.205
I am a doctor,

06:12.239 --> 06:14.475
which is why I am
bringing him this soup,

06:14.508 --> 06:16.009
homemade by me.

06:16.043 --> 06:18.446
Uh-huh?

06:20.047 --> 06:21.148
And what's this now?

06:21.181 --> 06:23.050
I had to use a can opener.

06:23.083 --> 06:24.818
That counts.

06:24.852 --> 06:27.655
Not in the South, it doesn't.

06:40.934 --> 06:42.836
I should have known.

06:42.870 --> 06:44.738
30 seconds
after George found out,

06:44.772 --> 06:46.306
you'd make your move.

06:46.339 --> 06:49.109
I didn't make my move,
I made soup.

06:49.142 --> 06:50.711
Listen to me,
little Miss Opportunistic,

06:50.744 --> 06:53.881
George may be angry at me,
but he will forgive me.

06:53.914 --> 06:56.517
In a couple of weeks, we will
be standing in that church,

06:56.550 --> 06:58.385
and we will be
saying our vows,

06:58.418 --> 07:01.221
and then we will be dancing
to "What a Wonderful World"

07:01.254 --> 07:03.557
in front of our 200
closest friends.

07:03.591 --> 07:06.426
And nothing and nobody
is gonna stop it.

07:06.460 --> 07:08.128
Lemon, I am simply
here because my friend,

07:08.161 --> 07:09.296
George, is in pain.

07:09.329 --> 07:10.998
He needs someone to talk to.

07:11.031 --> 07:13.266
Someone who didn't
break his heart.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.068
MAN:
Hey, George!

07:15.102 --> 07:17.304
*

07:30.317 --> 07:32.252
(fishing reel clicking)

07:38.692 --> 07:40.460
(cheering)

07:53.473 --> 07:55.042
Ladies, hi.

07:55.075 --> 07:57.845
Lemon, did you make
that cake for me?

07:57.878 --> 07:59.112
How thoughtful of you.

07:59.146 --> 08:02.249
And Zoe, is that...
is that soup?

08:03.016 --> 08:04.484
How sweet.

08:04.518 --> 08:06.119
Well,
you know what, ladies?

08:06.153 --> 08:07.655
I'll see you two later.

08:07.688 --> 08:08.856
Thanks for the grub.

08:16.163 --> 08:18.265
(cheerleaders chanting)

08:18.298 --> 08:20.834
(car horn honks)

08:20.868 --> 08:22.936
(seagulls calling)

08:22.970 --> 08:25.272
(birds singing)

08:33.013 --> 08:34.481
It was so weird.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.183
George Tucker was happy.

08:36.216 --> 08:37.684
Elated, even.

08:37.717 --> 08:39.886
It didn't even seem like
he was angry with me anymore.

08:39.919 --> 08:41.554
He is obviously in denial,

08:41.589 --> 08:43.523
which is stage one
in the five stages of grief.

08:43.557 --> 08:46.159
Yes, Zoe, even I,
the stupid football jock,

08:46.193 --> 08:47.561
knows what denial is.

08:47.595 --> 08:50.598
Sorry, I just...
I've never seen a case this bad.

08:50.631 --> 08:52.299
He needs to deal
with his feelings.

08:52.332 --> 08:54.935
I have to figure out a way
how to help him move on

08:54.968 --> 08:56.136
to stage two--

08:56.169 --> 08:57.571
anger-- before he snaps.

08:57.605 --> 08:59.640
And you're researching
how on a computer?

08:59.673 --> 09:01.975
Aren't you supposed
to be a doctor?

09:02.009 --> 09:03.510
Psych was not my best rotation.

09:03.543 --> 09:06.246
My thesis, "Get Over It,"
wasn't well received.

09:06.279 --> 09:07.314
Can't imagine why.

09:07.347 --> 09:08.649
The Internet is no help.

09:08.682 --> 09:11.251
It is telling me to let him be.

09:11.284 --> 09:13.053
It's unaware of the danger.

09:13.086 --> 09:15.355
Which is?
Which is he denies himself

09:15.388 --> 09:17.791
right down the aisle
with a woman who cheated on him.

09:17.825 --> 09:18.959
I see.

09:18.992 --> 09:20.160
Zoe?

09:20.193 --> 09:21.995
Maybe you should
just let this go.

09:22.029 --> 09:23.463
Oh, no, I cannot let this go.

09:23.496 --> 09:25.532
George's mental health
is in jeopardy.

09:25.565 --> 09:27.935
I have to get a consult.

09:32.172 --> 09:33.607
(piano playing)

09:33.641 --> 09:35.142
* I am the very model

09:35.175 --> 09:37.577
* Of a modern major general,
I've la-la-la-la *

09:37.611 --> 09:40.347
* Animal and la-la-la-la,
Benadryl *

09:40.380 --> 09:41.849
Benadryl, Brick?
You know, it's just hard

09:41.882 --> 09:44.818
for me to-to sing and...
with all these distractions.

09:44.852 --> 09:45.819
All right, all right.

09:45.853 --> 09:47.454
(piano resumes)

09:47.487 --> 09:50.023
* Know the kings of England and
a... (mumbles) *

09:50.057 --> 09:51.491
Tom?

09:51.524 --> 09:55.228
That boat is awesome.

09:55.262 --> 09:58.031
Will you pass the white paint?

09:58.065 --> 09:59.366
The white paint?

09:59.399 --> 10:01.201
Uh, uh...

10:01.234 --> 10:04.371
Sure, I'd... okay.

10:04.404 --> 10:06.106
(Brick continues)
Hey, Tom, buddy. Sweet tea?

10:06.139 --> 10:07.908
Yeah.
Wanda?

10:07.941 --> 10:09.209
Me?
Yeah.

10:09.242 --> 10:12.045
Brick, the performance
is tomorrow.

10:12.079 --> 10:14.014
You should have given me these
lyrics, like-like, a month ago.

10:14.047 --> 10:14.982
Well, I did.

10:15.015 --> 10:16.483
GEORGE:
Sweet tea, anyone?

10:16.516 --> 10:20.287
Hello, Lemon, would you like
some sweet tea?

10:20.320 --> 10:22.389
No, I-I do not want
a sweet tea.

10:22.422 --> 10:23.924
What the hell is going on?

10:23.957 --> 10:25.926
I believe that we are at
rehearsal for Dash's revue,

10:25.959 --> 10:28.228
and we are scheduled to sing
"I Am the Pirate King."

10:28.261 --> 10:30.998
Did something happen to you?
Are you okay?

10:31.031 --> 10:31.999
I'm fantastic.

10:32.032 --> 10:33.233
(Brick continues)
But you...

10:33.266 --> 10:35.335
you do remember
what happened last night?

10:35.368 --> 10:38.005
Oh, of course I remember.
Something like that's
hard to forget.

10:38.038 --> 10:41.374
All right, Brick. Come on,
next up is "Three Little
Maids from School."

10:41.408 --> 10:44.377
(piano playing lively intro)

10:44.411 --> 10:47.547
I am missing one little maid.

10:47.580 --> 10:51.551
Lemon... I think you're needed
on stage for rehearsal.

10:53.420 --> 10:55.856
Who's got a paintbrush for me?

11:04.531 --> 11:06.767
Hey, Shelley,
did you happen

11:06.800 --> 11:08.969
to see me leave here
last night with anyone?

11:09.002 --> 11:11.171
You were drunk and flirting
with every girl in here.

11:11.204 --> 11:12.172
Could've been anyone.

11:12.205 --> 11:13.673
You have any guesses?

11:15.876 --> 11:17.978
I guess her.
What'd you do that for?

11:18.011 --> 11:20.013
For calling me all drunk
for sex last night.

11:20.047 --> 11:21.749
Oh.

11:21.782 --> 11:23.751
Well, sorry.

11:23.784 --> 11:24.785
Here.

11:24.818 --> 11:25.685
(gasps)

11:25.719 --> 11:27.454
Like I would
ever wear that.

11:27.487 --> 11:28.822
So we didn't...?

11:28.856 --> 11:30.690
Of course not!
I turned you down.

11:30.724 --> 11:33.660
'Cause you'd already called
my married sister, you pig!

11:34.561 --> 11:36.797
Classy, Wade.

11:36.830 --> 11:37.597
Super classy!

11:37.630 --> 11:38.832
I wondered when you

11:38.866 --> 11:40.868
was gonna give me
that shirt back.

11:40.901 --> 11:44.037
This is not yours.
It's my sister's.

11:45.505 --> 11:47.808
Big Ethel?
I saw you when

11:47.841 --> 11:50.944
you snatched it
from my clothesline.
(relieved sigh)

11:50.978 --> 11:53.546
(chuckles):
Well... why-why
would I do that?

11:53.580 --> 11:56.716
Maybe 'cause you was
walking around naked
as the day is long.

11:56.750 --> 12:00.320
And you just keep
getting classier!

12:00.353 --> 12:01.989
(giggles)

12:02.022 --> 12:05.058
*

12:06.393 --> 12:09.129
"About binomial theorem,
I am teeming with a lot o' news,

12:09.162 --> 12:11.932
with many cheerful facts about
the square of the hypotenuse."

12:11.965 --> 12:13.300
Dear God.

12:13.333 --> 12:14.634
Yeah?
Hey.

12:14.667 --> 12:15.836
Hey. Hey.
Brick,

12:15.869 --> 12:17.737
have you ever dealt
with a patient

12:17.771 --> 12:19.506
who was stuck
in serious denial?

12:19.539 --> 12:21.708
(chuckles) First let me
relish the moment.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.477
(laughs) You've finally
come to me for a consult!

12:24.511 --> 12:26.513
Okay, okay, could we
please just get on with it?

12:26.546 --> 12:28.048
No, I'm still relishing.
(laughing)

12:28.081 --> 12:28.916
Brick!

12:28.949 --> 12:30.383
Oh, okay, okay.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.652
Well, you know,
a-a little short-term denial

12:32.685 --> 12:36.156
is a perfectly, uh,
healthy coping mechanism.

12:36.189 --> 12:38.525
Not in this case.
See, this guy just found out

12:38.558 --> 12:42.162
something terrible about
his fi... wife. His wife.

12:42.195 --> 12:45.198
Oh, I see, I see, mm-hmm.
Did Lemon put you up to this?

12:45.232 --> 12:46.266
What?
Dr. Hart,

12:46.299 --> 12:47.567
I am processing

12:47.600 --> 12:50.070
the information about my wife
in my own time,

12:50.103 --> 12:52.239
thank you very much,
and it is perfectly

12:52.272 --> 12:53.606
within reason for me to attend

12:53.640 --> 12:55.208
my own daughter's wedding
without a date.

12:55.242 --> 12:56.276
But I...
Now, if you will

12:56.309 --> 12:59.779
excuse me,
I have lines to learn.

12:59.813 --> 13:01.714
"I'm very good at integral
and differential calculus.

13:01.748 --> 13:03.616
"I... I know the
scientific names

13:03.650 --> 13:04.885
of beings animalculous." Yes!

13:04.918 --> 13:06.553
Yes, that's good, that's good.

13:06.586 --> 13:08.188
*

13:08.221 --> 13:10.757
* Three little maids who, all
unwary, come from a ladies' *

13:10.790 --> 13:13.693
* Seminary, freed
from its genius tutelary *

13:13.726 --> 13:16.396
* Three little maids
from school *

13:16.429 --> 13:18.298
* Three little maids

13:18.331 --> 13:19.566
* From school...

13:19.599 --> 13:21.835
*

13:21.869 --> 13:25.438
Wow. They're just lovely,
aren't they, Tom?

13:25.472 --> 13:28.408
Uh, uh... yes?

13:28.441 --> 13:29.676
Do you sing?

13:29.709 --> 13:32.079
Well... I...
(laughs)

13:32.112 --> 13:34.414
He's incredible.
Have you never heard
him in the church choir?

13:34.447 --> 13:36.183
Really fantastic voice.

13:36.216 --> 13:37.450
You know what?

13:37.484 --> 13:39.920
I think I'm gonna go
get some more paint.

13:39.953 --> 13:41.721
*

13:41.754 --> 13:43.423
(piano continues in distance)

13:43.456 --> 13:45.592
Thank you, sir.

13:45.625 --> 13:47.127
Oh, hey, Lemon.
Great rehearsal.

13:47.160 --> 13:49.096
You were really hitting
those high notes.
Stop it.

13:49.129 --> 13:51.164
Stop what? I thought I was
being perfectly friendly.

13:51.198 --> 13:52.399
Don't be friendly, George.

13:52.432 --> 13:54.467
Friendly is... insane, okay?

13:54.501 --> 13:56.703
I hurt you.
I betrayed you,

13:56.736 --> 13:59.839
so just yell at me
or scream at me or
something, please!

13:59.873 --> 14:01.041
There's no need for that.

14:01.074 --> 14:02.675
I get it-- you
had an affair,

14:02.709 --> 14:04.611
and I'm sure that you
are very, very sorry.

14:04.644 --> 14:06.279
I am so sorry.

14:06.313 --> 14:08.348
I am so, so, so, so sorry.

14:08.381 --> 14:10.750
Like I said,
I am sure you are.

14:10.783 --> 14:13.220
So does this... mean
that there's still hope

14:13.253 --> 14:14.621
for the wedding to be on?

14:14.654 --> 14:17.090
Not even an iota.

14:17.124 --> 14:18.591
DASH:
Lemon, George,

14:18.625 --> 14:20.160
come on, you're up.
You know what?

14:20.193 --> 14:21.962
I don't feel much like
rehearsing, and I got

14:21.995 --> 14:23.763
my part down pat,
so I'll just see you

14:23.796 --> 14:25.632
at the big show
tomorrow, okay?
What...?

14:25.665 --> 14:27.700
Wha...?
Thank you, Dash.

14:30.003 --> 14:31.171
*

14:31.204 --> 14:32.906
ZOE:
Hey.

14:32.940 --> 14:35.075
Hey, Zoe.
Hi, George.

14:35.108 --> 14:36.509
Hey, are we okay?

14:36.543 --> 14:37.710
Of course we are.

14:37.744 --> 14:39.446
Look... I want
to say I'm sorry

14:39.479 --> 14:41.381
for taking it all
out on you last night.

14:41.414 --> 14:44.051
I know that you were
just trying to do what's best.

14:44.084 --> 14:45.919
And, you know, you're
a really good friend--

14:45.953 --> 14:47.620
I just want
to tell you that.

14:47.654 --> 14:49.389
I am glad you
think so, pal.

14:49.422 --> 14:52.525
Hey, I was hoping
you might want to
watch a movie with me.

14:52.559 --> 14:54.061
Oh, yeah?
Yeah. I got, um,

14:54.094 --> 14:56.529
Unfaithful,
 Fatal Attraction,
(laughing)

14:56.563 --> 14:58.065
Obsessed...
Zoe...

14:58.098 --> 15:01.368
Look, George, I don't mean
to alarm you, but...

15:01.401 --> 15:04.337
all of that happiness you
feel is really major denial.

15:04.371 --> 15:05.605
It's not denial.

15:05.638 --> 15:07.674
And this happiness I feel...

15:07.707 --> 15:08.908
it's relief.

15:08.942 --> 15:10.677
See, I've been
walking around

15:10.710 --> 15:12.512
for six months
wondering why my fiancée

15:12.545 --> 15:13.947
was acting
all nutty and erratic,

15:13.981 --> 15:17.284
and now that I get it,
why, I feel...

15:17.317 --> 15:18.685
I feel free.

15:18.718 --> 15:21.088
Free?
Yeah. I get
to start over-- now,

15:21.121 --> 15:24.257
while I am still young
and vibrant and, let's face it,

15:24.291 --> 15:25.725
kind of cute.

15:26.693 --> 15:27.794
(laughs)

15:27.827 --> 15:29.129
All right, look, George,

15:29.162 --> 15:30.397
you need to process.

15:30.430 --> 15:31.664
No, no, no processing.

15:31.698 --> 15:34.034
See, what I need
to do... is live.

15:34.067 --> 15:36.236
Turns out that Lemon
wasn't the girl for me.

15:36.269 --> 15:37.637
She wasn't my destiny.

15:37.670 --> 15:40.173
So now it's my job
to go find out what...

15:40.207 --> 15:41.274
or who...

15:41.308 --> 15:44.044
that destiny is.

15:44.077 --> 15:46.679
Well, I guess that makes sense.

15:46.713 --> 15:49.849
So... Zoe Hart,

15:49.882 --> 15:54.454
I hope to see you around
again... really soon.

15:54.487 --> 15:57.024
*

16:10.137 --> 16:11.704
Yeah? That's it?

16:11.738 --> 16:13.406
Oh, Daddy,
not even close.

16:13.440 --> 16:17.010
If this were not charity,
I would quit it... right now.

16:18.545 --> 16:20.147
Are you okay, Lemon?

16:20.180 --> 16:21.481
You look kind of pale.

16:21.514 --> 16:23.416
No.
(scoffs):
Oh...

16:23.450 --> 16:25.652
it's all those
ridiculous hats she wears.

16:25.685 --> 16:26.786
She never gets

16:26.819 --> 16:28.321
any sun.
(laughs, sighs)

16:28.355 --> 16:29.756
I'm fine.

16:29.789 --> 16:30.923
I'm fine, Daddy.

16:30.957 --> 16:32.459
You stay healthy--
you know, this is

16:32.492 --> 16:35.528
a big month
for you, right?
Of course it is.

16:35.562 --> 16:37.164
You should really tell him.

16:37.197 --> 16:38.731
Oh, no, there's no need to.

16:38.765 --> 16:40.633
George and I are
gonna make it through.

16:40.667 --> 16:42.269
I have a new plan.

16:42.302 --> 16:45.205
What?
At the end of our Gilbert
and Sullivan song,

16:45.238 --> 16:48.508
I am gonna kiss him,
right there up on stage.

16:48.541 --> 16:49.742
And what?

16:49.776 --> 16:52.679
He'll get furious,
and fury will lead to a fight,

16:52.712 --> 16:55.014
and a fight will lead him
to let out his feelings,

16:55.048 --> 16:56.316
his anger, and we'll
talk through it,

16:56.349 --> 16:57.950
and then we'll live
happily, happily,

16:57.984 --> 16:59.452
happily, happily ever after.

16:59.486 --> 17:04.223
Whew. We really need to get
a shrink in this town.

17:05.192 --> 17:07.160
And if the girls club's

17:07.194 --> 17:09.996
gonna have its bake sale
on Wednesday, we'll need

17:10.029 --> 17:11.964
to change
the trash pickup.

17:11.998 --> 17:14.300
(frustrated sigh)

17:15.568 --> 17:18.137
(exhales)

17:21.973 --> 17:23.643
(light chuckle)
Uh...

17:23.675 --> 17:25.845
Selectwoman Blackwell,

17:25.877 --> 17:27.513
it has been a treat.
(chuckles)

17:27.547 --> 17:30.683
And, uh, I will
get back to you on
all those issues...

17:30.717 --> 17:32.585
promptly.

17:32.619 --> 17:33.853
Thank you, Mayor Hayes.

17:33.886 --> 17:35.188
Thank you for coming.

17:35.222 --> 17:38.591
All right.
You have a good old day.

17:38.625 --> 17:40.593
What is wrong with you?

17:40.627 --> 17:43.563
So very... very much.

17:43.596 --> 17:45.132
The shirt...

17:45.165 --> 17:47.434
was Ethel Warner's.

17:47.467 --> 17:48.735
No.

17:48.768 --> 17:50.870
No, no...

17:50.903 --> 17:52.939
No...
No, no, no, no. I...

17:52.972 --> 17:55.275
Apparently, I stole it
off her clothesline.

17:55.308 --> 17:56.976
Well, why'd you do that?

17:57.009 --> 17:59.679
Because I was naked.

17:59.712 --> 18:03.183
And I have no idea what
happened to my clothes.

18:03.216 --> 18:04.451
Or where my car is.

18:04.484 --> 18:06.786
Or why my arm is so damn itchy.

18:06.819 --> 18:08.020
That's a clue.

18:08.054 --> 18:09.489
Well, maybe it's an allergy.

18:09.522 --> 18:11.758
What are you allergic to?
Uh...

18:11.791 --> 18:14.794
pumpkins, birch beer, rabbits.

18:14.827 --> 18:18.030
Pumpkin season's over,
and I stay way the hell away

18:18.064 --> 18:20.400
from birch beer.

18:20.433 --> 18:23.770
Only person I know
with a pet rabbit is...

18:23.803 --> 18:26.139
Oh, dear God.
What?

18:26.173 --> 18:28.308
I know who exactly
who I was with last night.

18:28.341 --> 18:30.910
And I only wish it was
Big Ethel, 'cause this is...

18:30.943 --> 18:33.012
oh, this is so much worse.
Well, who could

18:33.045 --> 18:34.381
be worse than Big Ethel?

18:34.414 --> 18:35.382
Tansy.

18:35.415 --> 18:37.584
Your ex-wife.

18:37.617 --> 18:40.420
My ex-wife who's
still in love with me.

18:41.688 --> 18:43.690
God, I am such a jerk!

18:48.428 --> 18:49.929
*

18:49.962 --> 18:53.333
(motorcycle rumbling)

19:00.173 --> 19:02.375
So I see, you're not in denial,

19:02.409 --> 19:04.477
you're in an
erectile dysfunction ad.

19:04.511 --> 19:06.579
(chuckles):
Oh-ho...
Ha-ha. What is going on?

19:06.613 --> 19:10.550
Just realized that I'd been
part of an us for so long
that I'd lost sight of me,

19:10.583 --> 19:14.187
so I stayed up all
night and I made a list
of things, that, uh...

19:14.221 --> 19:16.823
that I want to do.
And one was dying

19:16.856 --> 19:18.057
in a motorcycle accident?
No, no.

19:18.090 --> 19:19.826
No, 'cause I have a
helmet, Doctor.

19:19.859 --> 19:21.060
Oh, good.

19:21.093 --> 19:23.496
What else is on this list?
Oh, so much.

19:23.530 --> 19:25.332
So much. A couple
of years ago,

19:25.365 --> 19:27.367
Lemon and I, we
went to New Orleans,

19:27.400 --> 19:29.969
and I saw this little
place, Bar Moreau.

19:30.002 --> 19:32.339
It had this incredible
old-time jazz band,

19:32.372 --> 19:34.507
it was decked out,
the place was amazing.

19:34.541 --> 19:37.977
I wanted to go in,
but Lemon wanted to
go to the opera.

19:38.010 --> 19:39.846
So... I'm going there now.

19:39.879 --> 19:42.349
Aren't you supposed to be
in Dash's revue tonight?

19:42.382 --> 19:44.016
Also something that Lemon
wanted to do, not me.

19:44.050 --> 19:46.386
And I'm not doing things
I don't want to do anymore.

19:46.419 --> 19:47.720
It is George Tucker time.

19:47.754 --> 19:49.188
(laughs):
Okay.

19:49.222 --> 19:50.823
You have fun.

19:50.857 --> 19:52.259
Oh, I will.

19:52.292 --> 19:53.826
Okay.
(chuckles)

19:53.860 --> 19:55.194
You have fun here.

19:55.228 --> 19:56.729
Oh, thanks.

19:57.897 --> 19:59.732
(sighs)
Don't die.

19:59.766 --> 20:02.168
*

20:09.175 --> 20:11.010
Hey, Tansy.
Hey.

20:11.043 --> 20:12.279
Thank you...

20:12.312 --> 20:13.880
for bringing my car back.

20:13.913 --> 20:15.248
It's the least I could do.

20:15.282 --> 20:17.750
And I'm sorry for,
uh... you know...

20:17.784 --> 20:19.118
(clears throat)

20:19.151 --> 20:21.421
...having drunk sex
with you last night.

20:21.454 --> 20:24.391
(laughs) Is that
what you think happened?

20:24.424 --> 20:27.560
Well, you were drunk,
but we did not have sex.

20:27.594 --> 20:29.128
We didn't?
Oh, you wanted to.

20:29.161 --> 20:31.298
You even took off your clothes

20:31.331 --> 20:32.432
to prove how much.

20:32.465 --> 20:33.866
But last time
I saw you,

20:33.900 --> 20:35.001
you gave me a speech

20:35.034 --> 20:36.168
about making better choices,

20:36.202 --> 20:37.270
and you were right.

20:37.304 --> 20:39.038
Which is why I kicked you out.

20:39.071 --> 20:41.007
Guess you were too
drunk to figure out

20:41.040 --> 20:42.775
how to put your
clothes back on.

20:42.809 --> 20:44.176
(laughs)

20:44.210 --> 20:47.447
Well, thank you
for having some good sense.

20:47.480 --> 20:49.649
At least one of us does.

20:49.682 --> 20:52.051
I'm trying.

20:52.084 --> 20:54.654
Actually, I'm going
to night school,

20:54.687 --> 20:55.822
studying cosmetology.

20:55.855 --> 20:57.023
Hey, all right!

20:57.056 --> 20:59.459
And I am steering clear
of men for now.

20:59.492 --> 21:01.461
I'm getting
my life together, and...

21:01.494 --> 21:04.096
it's all because of you
being so terrible to me.

21:04.130 --> 21:06.265
So thanks.
(chuckles)

21:06.299 --> 21:08.535
I should grab a cab.

21:08.568 --> 21:10.803
Yeah.
I have to study.

21:13.272 --> 21:16.509
*

21:20.513 --> 21:22.915
Well, it's not broken,
just a bad bruise.

21:22.949 --> 21:24.116
You are lucky.

21:24.150 --> 21:26.018
I got distracted
while I was hammering.

21:26.052 --> 21:28.220
I know I should've been
looking at what I was doing.

21:28.254 --> 21:29.689
It's just...

21:29.722 --> 21:31.858
I kinda have
a crush on someone.

21:31.891 --> 21:33.092
Anyone I know?

21:33.125 --> 21:35.962
Do you know Tom Long?
Tom... Long?

21:35.995 --> 21:37.764
You have a crush on Tom Long?

21:37.797 --> 21:39.399
Who wouldn't?

21:39.432 --> 21:44.103
He's sweet and funny and
handsome and good to his mama.

21:44.136 --> 21:46.339
He's just so shy.

21:46.373 --> 21:48.408
(cell phone rings)

21:48.441 --> 21:50.677
Hold that thought.

21:50.710 --> 21:51.911
Hello?

21:51.944 --> 21:53.980
Zoe Hart? I just wanted
to call and tell you

21:54.013 --> 21:56.783
that you are missing out,
because New Orleans is amazing.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.985
I mean, it's alive,
it's electric.

21:59.018 --> 22:01.454
And the food! I'm eating this
beignet right now,

22:01.488 --> 22:04.290
and I swear to you,
it is a religious experience.

22:04.323 --> 22:05.992
Well, I am glad
you are having fun.

22:06.025 --> 22:08.094
You know, you should
come join me.
W-W-What?

22:08.127 --> 22:10.597
New Orleans is like two hours
away. You come out here,

22:10.630 --> 22:12.699
we'll hang out, we'll,
uh, hear some jazz.

22:12.732 --> 22:14.501
And then you'd be home by
1:00 a.m., 2:00 at the latest.

22:14.534 --> 22:16.035
I don't know...
Oh, come on. Doc, hey.

22:16.068 --> 22:18.070
You need to get yourself
out of that stuffy office.

22:18.104 --> 22:20.840
You need to live a little. You
need to seize the day, Zoe Hart.

22:20.873 --> 22:23.042
Seize the day!
I'll think about it.

22:23.075 --> 22:24.210
Well, you do that.

22:24.243 --> 22:25.878
You think about that
real hard.

22:25.912 --> 22:28.381
Okay?
Bye.

22:31.551 --> 22:32.685
So, what do you think?

22:32.719 --> 22:34.521
What should I
do about Tom Long?

22:34.554 --> 22:36.122
I think you should
go for it.

22:36.155 --> 22:37.424
Really?
Sometimes...

22:37.457 --> 22:38.725
destiny gives us a window,

22:38.758 --> 22:40.593
and no matter how
crazy it may seem,

22:40.627 --> 22:43.362
you have to act on it
before that window closes.

22:43.396 --> 22:44.697
I have to go.

22:46.265 --> 22:48.367
(orchestral music plays)

22:50.269 --> 22:53.440
I just want to let you know
that George still isn't here.

22:53.473 --> 22:54.707
He's not?
Mm-mm.

22:54.741 --> 22:56.976
That's okay.
He will be.

22:57.009 --> 22:58.445
I'm not worried.

22:58.478 --> 23:00.913
First up is "Three Little
Maids." And for me,

23:00.947 --> 23:02.048
two little ear plugs.

23:02.081 --> 23:03.716
Come on.

23:03.750 --> 23:06.619
Magnolia, you get him
here, okay?

23:06.653 --> 23:09.255
Everything depends on this.
Everything.
Okay.

23:09.288 --> 23:11.390
Thank you.
Okay. Go, go, go.

23:15.462 --> 23:19.065
Lavon! Lavon, I need
to borrow your car

23:19.098 --> 23:22.168
and some cash for emergencies
and directions to New Orleans.

23:22.201 --> 23:24.303
And why are you going
to New Orleans?
To meet George.

23:24.336 --> 23:26.439
Dangerous territory, Zoe.
Very dangerous.

23:26.473 --> 23:29.509
But what if George
is my destiny,

23:29.542 --> 23:31.343
and this is my only chance?

23:32.344 --> 23:34.981
Let me remind you of one thing.

23:35.014 --> 23:37.383
George did not choose you.

23:37.416 --> 23:39.452
He found out
a secret about Lemon.

23:39.486 --> 23:40.853
Big difference.

23:50.463 --> 23:51.898
(lively piano tune plays)

