*

26:08.234 --> 26:10.269
I did not know that
you could sing like that.

26:10.302 --> 26:11.804
Well, there are
a lot of things

26:11.838 --> 26:13.773
you don't know
about me, Zoe Hart.
I guess so.

26:16.175 --> 26:17.810
But I'm really
glad you came.

26:17.844 --> 26:21.280
'Cause now you can help me with
the next thing on my to-do list.

26:21.313 --> 26:23.282
Bartender,
two Hurricanes, please.

26:23.315 --> 26:24.516
I'm sorry to interrupt.

26:24.550 --> 26:26.018
But you were
great up there.

26:26.052 --> 26:27.553
Oh, thank you.

26:27.586 --> 26:29.121
Can we see you perform
anywhere else in town?

26:29.155 --> 26:32.124
Um, sorry,
that was actually
Hm.

26:32.158 --> 26:34.160
just kind
of a spontaneous thing, so...

26:34.193 --> 26:35.895
Oh.
But you are
a professional singer?

26:35.928 --> 26:36.863
(laughs)

26:36.896 --> 26:38.497
GEORGE:
No.

26:38.530 --> 26:40.432
Really? Actually, I'm a lawyer.

26:40.466 --> 26:43.302
You hear that, honey?
We're groupies for a lawyer.

26:43.335 --> 26:44.937
Oh, don't be embarrassed.

26:44.971 --> 26:47.339
You're not the first groupies
that this lawyer has had.

26:47.373 --> 26:49.308
Kim and Pablo Charlton.

26:49.341 --> 26:51.443
Um, George Tucker.
Hi, I'm Zoe.

26:51.477 --> 26:53.112
Hi.
You two from around here?

26:53.145 --> 26:55.715
No, we're just visiting.
Oh, so are we.
From New Jersey.

26:55.748 --> 26:57.216
Actually, we're
on our honeymoon.

26:57.249 --> 26:58.517
Oh, congratulations.

26:58.550 --> 27:01.053
And that is such a
coincidence, because...

27:01.087 --> 27:04.056
so are we.

27:04.090 --> 27:06.292
(chuckles)

27:08.127 --> 27:10.997
* I'm called Little Buttercup

27:11.030 --> 27:12.799
* Dear Little Buttercup

27:12.832 --> 27:16.602
* Though I could
never tell why... *

27:16.635 --> 27:18.170
Did you hear?
I got all the words right.

27:18.204 --> 27:19.806
Every single one!
(chuckles)

27:19.839 --> 27:21.007
Where's Lemon?

27:21.040 --> 27:22.608
Um... not really sure.
(nervous laugh)

27:22.641 --> 27:25.778
* Sweet Little Buttercup Pie

27:25.812 --> 27:28.414
We are going to have to
skip their number.

27:28.447 --> 27:31.083
Tom and I can fill in.

27:31.117 --> 27:32.919
Oh, he can sing.
He's in the choir.

27:32.952 --> 27:34.353
We can do it!
What...?

27:34.386 --> 27:35.822
* ...Pie!

27:35.855 --> 27:37.690
(song ends)

27:37.724 --> 27:38.925
Come on, Tom.

27:38.958 --> 27:40.626
Seize the day.

27:40.659 --> 27:42.628
Okay, we can do it.
(chuckles)

27:44.430 --> 27:46.733
(audience murmurs)

27:49.401 --> 27:50.770
(piano plays steady tune)

27:50.803 --> 27:53.773
* Oh, better far
to live and die *

27:53.806 --> 27:55.808
* Under the brave black
flag I fly *

27:55.842 --> 27:58.344
* Than play a
sanctimonious part *

27:58.377 --> 28:02.815
* With a pirate head
and a pirate heart *

28:02.849 --> 28:07.419
* Away to the
cheating world go you *

28:07.453 --> 28:10.589
* Where pirates are all
well-to-do. *

28:10.622 --> 28:13.459
* But I'll be true to
the song I sing *

28:13.492 --> 28:18.330
* And live and die
a Pirate King *

28:18.364 --> 28:23.669
* For I am a Pirate King

28:23.702 --> 28:26.172
* And it is, it is
a glorious thing *

28:26.205 --> 28:28.307
* To be a Pirate King

28:28.340 --> 28:30.676
* For I am
a Pirate King *

28:30.709 --> 28:32.812
* You are, hurrah for
the Pirate King! *

28:32.845 --> 28:35.381
* And it is, it is
a glorious thing... *

28:35.414 --> 28:37.116
Where are Lemon and George?

28:37.149 --> 28:38.717
It's not like them
to-to blow off

28:38.751 --> 28:41.053
an important talent event
and to miss my song.

28:41.087 --> 28:45.357
Daddy,
I have to tell you something.

28:45.391 --> 28:47.026
* ...to be
a Pirate King, it is! *

28:47.059 --> 28:52.164
* Hurrah for the Pirate King,
hurrah for the Pirate King! *

28:52.198 --> 28:55.667
(cheering and applause)

29:00.739 --> 29:02.708
KIM: So you don't
live anywhere?

29:02.741 --> 29:04.643
No, right now,
nothing's holding us down.

29:04.676 --> 29:06.678
We're just kind of,
untethered, free.

29:06.712 --> 29:09.215
You know, so we decided
to take a year off

29:09.248 --> 29:11.250
and travel...
Yeah.

29:11.283 --> 29:12.518
and see where
life takes us.

29:12.551 --> 29:14.887
Yeah, well we've
been all over.

29:14.921 --> 29:16.488
To Australia.
Oh, yeah.

29:16.522 --> 29:18.690
Europe...
Wow, so what's next?

29:18.724 --> 29:22.461
Uh, what's next on the
honeymoon is Uganda, actually.

29:22.494 --> 29:24.363
I have always wanted
to go to Uganda,

29:24.396 --> 29:26.765
to see the gorillas
in the wild.

29:26.799 --> 29:28.600
Me, too.

29:28.634 --> 29:31.871
KIM: You two lead
such an amazing life.

29:31.904 --> 29:34.706
We really do.
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentlemen...

29:34.740 --> 29:37.910
we have a special guest
performer tonight.

29:37.944 --> 29:41.213
Please give a warm
New Orleans welcome

29:41.247 --> 29:44.050
to Mr. Scotty McCreery.

29:44.083 --> 29:47.887
(cheering and applause)

29:51.523 --> 29:53.392
Scotty McCreery, holy crap!

29:53.425 --> 29:56.695
If you'll excuse us, I, uh...

29:56.728 --> 29:58.965
I'm gonna go
dance with my bride.

29:58.998 --> 30:01.633
*

30:01.667 --> 30:02.634
Come on.

30:02.668 --> 30:04.003
(chuckles)

30:04.036 --> 30:07.806
* The trouble with girls
is they're a mystery *

30:07.840 --> 30:11.510
* Something about them
puzzles me *

30:11.543 --> 30:14.914
* I spend my whole life trying
to figure out *

30:14.947 --> 30:18.684
* Just what them girls
are all about *

30:18.717 --> 30:21.988
* The trouble with girls is
they're so dang pretty... *

30:22.021 --> 30:25.757
I should have known that we
would have so much in common.

30:26.425 --> 30:27.927
Zoe Hart,

30:27.960 --> 30:31.563
from the first day I picked you
up by the side of the road,

30:31.597 --> 30:33.465
you have gotten to me.

30:33.499 --> 30:35.701
It's been a great night.

30:37.003 --> 30:40.706
Do you have anything left on
your list that you want to do?

30:40.739 --> 30:42.041
*

30:42.074 --> 30:45.777
You know, I've done
every thing on my list.

30:47.346 --> 30:49.548
Except one...

30:49.581 --> 30:51.483
* They steal you with "Hello"

30:51.517 --> 30:54.686
* They kill you with
"Good-bye" *

30:54.720 --> 30:58.257
* They're the perfect drug

30:58.290 --> 31:01.860
* And I can't break free

31:01.894 --> 31:06.498
* Yeah, the trouble with girls

31:06.532 --> 31:12.471
* Is nobody loves
trouble as much as me. *

31:30.889 --> 31:33.559
So, what now?

31:33.592 --> 31:35.561
*

31:35.594 --> 31:37.729
Now...

31:37.763 --> 31:39.798
Now we spend the night.

31:39.831 --> 31:41.200
(chuckles)

31:41.233 --> 31:43.302
And be who we
just pretended we were,

31:43.335 --> 31:45.271
live our lives.

31:45.304 --> 31:47.273
Seize the day.

31:48.740 --> 31:50.042
You're right,
we should.

31:51.410 --> 31:52.644
We should.
Yeah.

31:52.678 --> 31:54.947
I'll get us a room, then.

31:54.981 --> 31:56.748
My mom knows somebody

31:56.782 --> 31:58.484
at every fancy hotel
in America.

31:58.517 --> 32:01.587
So, why don't you
let me make the call?

32:05.524 --> 32:07.526
*

32:16.868 --> 32:19.038
George?

32:19.071 --> 32:21.974
George, are you in there?!

32:22.008 --> 32:24.376
George?
BRICK:
Lemon?

32:25.811 --> 32:27.879
Hi, Daddy.

32:27.913 --> 32:31.050
Um... I was just, um...

32:31.083 --> 32:33.219
I was just checking to see

32:33.252 --> 32:36.322
if Zoe Hart had my wallet,
because I lost it,

32:36.355 --> 32:38.390
and somebody said
that she might have it.

32:38.424 --> 32:41.393
And I-I need to find it,
because it's really important.

32:41.427 --> 32:46.598
Honey, Magnolia told me
George broke off the wedding.

32:46.632 --> 32:48.134
What's going on?

32:49.601 --> 32:51.603
I messed up real bad.

32:53.572 --> 32:55.607
I messed up so bad, Daddy.

32:57.509 --> 32:59.445
I cheated on George.

32:59.478 --> 33:01.347
(murmurs)

33:02.714 --> 33:04.483
(sobbing)

33:09.921 --> 33:12.124
*

33:13.459 --> 33:15.194
Oh. Hey, Tom.

33:15.227 --> 33:18.830
So, I hear you solved
the mystery.
Yeah. Yeah, I did.

33:18.864 --> 33:20.032
I'm sorry I couldn't be there

33:20.066 --> 33:22.168
to lend a hand,
but I had a big night.

33:22.201 --> 33:26.272
I was so scared, but... I sang.

33:26.305 --> 33:28.974
Hey. Hey, that's great.

33:29.007 --> 33:30.376
It was incredible.

33:30.409 --> 33:32.378
Up there on that stage
with Wanda,

33:32.411 --> 33:34.080
it felt like
everything was right.

33:34.113 --> 33:36.448
It felt like, uh, destiny.

33:36.482 --> 33:38.984
Destiny, huh?
I've been

33:39.017 --> 33:40.186
pining away for Zoe Hart

33:40.219 --> 33:43.622
for so long
that I nearly missed Wanda.

33:43.655 --> 33:45.357
Well, good for you.

33:45.391 --> 33:48.394
You know, I'm, uh...
I'm glad you found someone.

33:48.427 --> 33:50.929
Our life as wild bachelors
was incredible,

33:50.962 --> 33:52.898
but it's time to grow up.

33:52.931 --> 33:54.566
I'm nearly 23.

33:54.600 --> 33:58.370
I'm sorry, Wade...
but good-bye.

34:00.606 --> 34:02.674
All right, Tom.

34:09.915 --> 34:12.118
(phone beeps)

34:14.186 --> 34:17.822
Hey, Tansy, it's, uh...
it's Wade.

34:17.856 --> 34:21.893
(crowd chatter,
jazz playing)

34:21.927 --> 34:23.862
Pierre, a suite
would be perfect.

34:23.895 --> 34:25.964
Thank you so much.
Okay, bye.

34:25.996 --> 34:29.701
* I see trees of green

34:29.735 --> 34:33.071
* Red roses, too

34:33.105 --> 34:38.344
* I see them bloom
for me and for you *

34:38.377 --> 34:43.081
* And I think to myself

34:43.114 --> 34:47.386
* What a wonderful world

34:51.523 --> 34:55.327
* I see skies of blue

34:55.360 --> 34:59.265
* And clouds of white

34:59.298 --> 35:01.567
* The bright, blessed day

35:01.600 --> 35:04.470
* And the dark, sacred night

35:04.503 --> 35:09.541
* And I think to myself

35:09.575 --> 35:15.714
* What a wonderful world

35:17.616 --> 35:20.552
* I see friends shaking hands

35:20.586 --> 35:24.190
* Saying, "How do you do?"

35:24.223 --> 35:27.893
* They're really saying

35:27.926 --> 35:30.162
* I love you

35:30.196 --> 35:32.164
* I see skies of blue...

35:32.198 --> 35:34.766
Your wedding song.

35:34.800 --> 35:35.834
* And clouds of white

35:35.867 --> 35:38.304
It just took me by
surprise, that's all.

35:38.337 --> 35:40.306
* The bright, blessed day

35:40.339 --> 35:42.608
* And the dark, sacred night

35:42.641 --> 35:44.276
George...

35:44.310 --> 35:47.012
* And I think to myself

35:47.045 --> 35:50.048
...I think it's time to go home.

35:50.081 --> 35:53.819
* What a wonderful world

35:54.953 --> 35:59.625
* What a wonderful world.

36:12.671 --> 36:14.773
Wow! Nice hair.

36:14.806 --> 36:16.074
Very funny.

36:16.107 --> 36:18.244
We have to practice on
each other in class,

36:18.277 --> 36:20.045
and my partner went
a little overboard.

36:20.078 --> 36:22.614
No, no. It, uh...
it looks good.

36:22.648 --> 36:23.849
(laughs)

36:23.882 --> 36:26.017
Thank you for, uh...
for coming by.

36:26.051 --> 36:27.152
You're my only ex-husband.

36:27.185 --> 36:29.755
When you need
me, I'm here.

36:29.788 --> 36:30.622
What's going on?

36:30.656 --> 36:31.990
Well, you know, I was...

36:32.023 --> 36:33.292
I was just thinking

36:33.325 --> 36:35.227
about what you said,
about, uh...

36:35.261 --> 36:36.895
you know, about how
you're trying to change

36:36.928 --> 36:39.365
and-and do better, and, uh,

36:39.398 --> 36:40.832
well, it got me thinking.

36:40.866 --> 36:43.168
Getting drunk,

36:43.201 --> 36:46.672
going home with random women,
losing my clothes...

36:46.705 --> 36:47.773
(laughs)

36:47.806 --> 36:49.441
...I'm trying to put that
behind me, too.

36:49.475 --> 36:51.410
Is that so?
Obviously, I'm...

36:51.443 --> 36:52.911
I'm not doing perfectly.

36:52.944 --> 36:54.513
(laughs)
But, uh,

36:54.546 --> 36:55.714
I got a plan.

36:55.747 --> 36:58.049
I'm-I'm saving up money
to open my own bar.

36:58.083 --> 37:00.185
I think it could be
a pretty special place.

37:00.218 --> 37:02.053
Is that why you called me?

37:02.087 --> 37:04.189
To tell me
you're saving up for a bar?

37:04.222 --> 37:06.892
I guess I just wanted you
to know that, uh...

37:06.925 --> 37:10.329
well, I'm-I'm trying, too.

37:12.264 --> 37:14.833
Well, it's about time,
Wade Kinsella.

37:15.867 --> 37:18.770
(both laugh)

37:26.712 --> 37:28.680
Zoe, thank you...

37:28.714 --> 37:30.716
for everything.

37:32.851 --> 37:34.820
This night was magical.

37:34.853 --> 37:36.888
But...

37:36.922 --> 37:40.892
When the magic wears off,
reality will still be here.

37:40.926 --> 37:44.296
And you have to deal with it.

37:45.130 --> 37:46.898
Yeah.

37:46.932 --> 37:49.335
I'll see you tomorrow.

38:03.949 --> 38:04.883
Hey, George.

38:04.916 --> 38:05.917
(groans)

38:08.420 --> 38:10.622
(Lavon groans)

38:13.959 --> 38:15.961
Okay, I-I... I
did feel that.

38:18.364 --> 38:20.332
(Lavon sighs)

38:20.366 --> 38:22.300
I'm sorry, Daddy.

38:22.334 --> 38:26.137
You must be
so disappointed in me.

38:26.171 --> 38:28.974
No.

38:29.007 --> 38:31.109
We all make mistakes.

38:31.142 --> 38:34.279
All of us do. It's okay.

38:37.783 --> 38:42.187
Do you think George...
is gonna come back?

38:44.456 --> 38:46.892
I don't know.

38:48.427 --> 38:50.596
Tell you what I do know.

38:50.629 --> 38:52.964
(crying)

38:52.998 --> 38:55.467
Unlike your dear old dad,

38:55.501 --> 39:00.406
you... are resilient.

39:01.740 --> 39:04.142
No matter what happens,
you will go on.

39:04.175 --> 39:06.745
That much I know.

39:10.382 --> 39:13.318
I can't sleep.
Is everything okay?

39:14.853 --> 39:17.856
Hey, Magpie, why don't
you go on back to bed?

39:17.889 --> 39:20.125
You know? I mean, you
got school tomorrow.

39:20.158 --> 39:21.693
I want to help.

39:21.727 --> 39:22.928
What can I do?

39:22.961 --> 39:26.498
Um, you can, um...

39:28.900 --> 39:32.203
...make a list of all the people
that we need to call

39:32.237 --> 39:34.740
to tell them
that the wedding is off.

39:34.773 --> 39:39.210
Okay, but don't make me
call Aunt Lavinia.

39:39.244 --> 39:40.846
(laughs)

39:40.879 --> 39:43.782
(knocking)

39:52.724 --> 39:55.461
*

40:13.278 --> 40:15.581
George, where have you been?

40:18.116 --> 40:19.751
Are you okay?

40:19.785 --> 40:21.352
(sighs)

40:21.386 --> 40:23.354
How could you...

40:23.388 --> 40:25.256
do that, Lemon?

40:25.290 --> 40:27.258
How...

40:27.292 --> 40:28.994
How could you do that to me?

40:29.027 --> 40:31.830
How could you
do that to us?

40:31.863 --> 40:32.864
I loved you, Lemon.

40:32.898 --> 40:35.100
So, no, I am not okay.

40:35.133 --> 40:38.136
I am hurt, and I am...
I am angry!

40:38.169 --> 40:40.371
(crying)
I know.

40:41.306 --> 40:43.509
I know.

40:45.811 --> 40:48.246
(crying)

40:48.279 --> 40:50.482
(groans softly)

40:51.683 --> 40:53.384
So, how was New Orleans?

40:53.418 --> 40:55.220
I had a perfect night.

40:55.253 --> 40:57.055
Well, almost perfect.

40:57.088 --> 40:58.557
But you were right.

40:58.590 --> 41:01.192
It's too soon for George
to start a new relationship.

41:01.226 --> 41:02.761
So I'm glad that we came home

41:02.794 --> 41:04.796
before we both did
something we'd regret.

41:07.298 --> 41:10.101
You seem oddly, uh...

41:10.135 --> 41:11.803
What is that look on your face?

41:11.837 --> 41:13.572
Hope.

41:13.605 --> 41:16.642
'Cause now I know
that George and I would be...

41:16.675 --> 41:19.144
that we could be great together.

41:19.177 --> 41:21.312
Wow.

41:21.346 --> 41:23.649
I really hope
everything works out for you.

41:25.316 --> 41:26.618
I do.

41:51.409 --> 41:53.579
*

